-- GNC agrees to be acquired by Ares, pension plan
-- 
-- Fri Feb 9, 2007 10:31am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/09/us-gnc-ares-idUSWEN404720070209

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - GNC Corp. ( GNC.N ), the leading retailer of vitamins and nutrition products, agreed to be acquired by Ares Management LLC and the Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan in a deal with a total enterprise value of $1.65 billion. 


 In a statement on Friday, Ares and Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan said Apollo Management LP, which owns about 97 percent of GNC's common stock and controls all of the voting rights, approved the transaction.